data.name: Tofu and Rice Bowl
data.quickTastyDescription: A simple and satisfying bowl of fluffy rice topped with sautéed tofu and fresh vegetables.
detailedCookingInstructions: Press the tofu to remove excess moisture, then cut it into cubes.
Heat olive oil in a non-stick skillet over medium heat.
Add the cubed tofu to the skillet and cook until golden brown on all sides, about 8-10 minutes.
Add the broccoli and carrot to the skillet and sauté for an additional 5 minutes until the vegetables are tender.
Pour the soy sauce over the tofu and vegetables, stirring to combine and heat through.
Serve the tofu and vegetable mixture over cooked rice, garnishing with chopped green onions and sesame seeds.
data.detailedName: Sautéed Tofu and Vegetable Rice Bowl
